st leave my child alone in a room in the middle of the night to pick up bug spray that you should be bringing up to me...Their laid back dont care attitudes is nothing short of annoying and downright rude.. I guess its true, You really do get what you pay for.I wouldnt recommend this hotel, I also found the safety of that part of the french quarter questionable to say the least. The minute I walked out my door I was getting asked for money..Its really a shame. For going on ten years now I have wanted to go to New Orleans and I found it not even close to what I had imagined it to be. It really is a place for a good party, I wont deny that. If you have children though I'd tell you to steer clear of New Orleans, there is nothing for families and dont be walkin around the quarter at dark, especially not by yourself. If you do go to New Orleans youre better of staying in Royal St, sure it might be loud, its only a block away from Bourbon, but everything you need is there and Jackon Sq is relatively close. I loved my time in America, ill be coming back soon, but I wont ever go back to New Orleans, its nothing but a big trash can with nice balconies.. 
